author: COMSOL
description: Every electrical device has some resistance. That is, when a voltage difference is applied across any two terminals of the device, a directly proportional current flow results. This example demonstrates how to compute the resistance of a short section of copper wire. The convergence of the solution with respect to the mesh size is also studied.
